<p>Fourth year of the victorious king Dantivarman <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kō-vicaiya-tanti-vikkiramaparumaṉ</foreign></supplied>.</p>
<p>Aṭavi, the lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kiḻavaṉ</foreign></supplied> of Tiruppālaiyūr in Perumpālaiyūr in the district <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kōṭṭam</foreign></supplied> of Ūṟṟukkāṭu, after having made request to the glorious Gaṅga king, the lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>perumāṉār</foreign></supplied> Nērkuṭṭi, the sluice <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tūmpu</foreign></supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">named</supplied> Kumāṟavāy that he had made.</p>
</div>

